    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 9800 - CAB - TILT: 9800 - LUBRICATION</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="lubricate" graphiccount="0">
        <title>LUBRICATION</title>
        <para>There are a number of points on the cab where periodic application of lubricant will increase the service
            life of the parts as well as eliminate objectionable squeaking.
        </para>
        <para>Following are points on the cab to be lubricated and the type of lubricant to use. Wipe off all
            lubrication points before applying new lubricant. When lubricating these points, apply lubricant sparingly
            so as not to allow excess lubricant to get on the operator's clothing.
        </para>
        <seqlist>
            <item>
                <para>Cab Latch Linkage - Light Engine Oil</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Door Lock Cylinder - Lock Oil</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Door Latch Striker Pin - Stick Lube</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Door Check Arm - Stick Lube</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Door Lock Assembly - Stick Lube</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Door Window Regulator Arm Pin and Slide - International 251HEP</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Seat Adjuster - International 251HEP</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Cab Door Latch - International 251HEP</para>
            </item>
            <item>
                <para>Heating A/C Control Cables - Silicone "200" Lube.</para>
            </item>
        </seqlist>
    </svcproc>
